        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "3402e6c6517cc15f159b19bf4462279285cd83f2",
            "subject": "LU-1571 mdt: Do not update xid for open replay req"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2012-11-02 09:11:23.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2012-11-08 04:34:13.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-2258 mount: solve races between evict and umount",
        "message": "LU-2258 mount: solve races between evict and umount\n\nThere are two race conditions between evict and umount.\n\n1) The one is that obd_export_evict_by_xxx() can touch a lustre hash\nwhich has already been finalized but not unregistered yet.\n\n2) The other is that the class_decref() in lprocfs_wr_evict_client()\ncan call lprocfs_remove() via osc_cleanup() while having _lprocfs_lock\nalready. That's why this case ends up in a deadlock.\n\nThis patch solve these problems with the below solutions.\n- see if obd_nid_hash and obd_uuid_hash is still available when\n  evicting.\n- move class_incref() to below LPROCFS_EXIT() and class_decref()\n  before LPROCFS_ENTRY() in order to avoid dead-locking\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: I2cc19a88ffd6a230ab115bc1e4b9d31fbbbb4615\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
